FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - BULGARIA (16): (BURGAS) OIE
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 21 Mar 2011
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2011; 24(12) [edited]
<http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=10386>


Foot-and-mouth disease, Bulgaria
--------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 19 Mar 2011 from Mr Nikola T
Belev, [president of the OIE Regional Commission for Europe, delegate
to the OIE, OIE regional representation for Europe], Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 6
Start date: 4 Jan 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 4 Jan 2011
Report date: 19 Mar 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Mar 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: October 1996
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports
- Immediate notification (7 Jan 2011)
- Follow-up report no 1 (11 Jan 2011)
- Follow-up report no 2 (17 Jan 2011)
- Follow-up report no 3 (31 Jan 2011)
- Follow-up report no 4 (14 Feb 2011)
- Follow-up report no 5 (25 Feb 2011)
- Follow-up report no 6 (19 Mar 2011)

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Kirovo village, Burgas, Burgas
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Mar 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 143 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the infected farm is located in the west part of
Strandja Mountain, municipality of Sredets, Burgas region, at a
distance of 7 km [4.4 mi] from the Turkish border, 3 km [1.9 mi] from
the closest village, Kirovo, located in the same municipality. In the
farm there are 143 bovines. No other animal species are kept there.
The animals are kept only for meat production at free range in a 400
hectares [988 acres] area surrounded by a fence. No animals have
entered or left the farm during the past 3 months.

Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate /
Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.70 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or
inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: on 19 Mar 2011, the National Reference
Laboratory confirmed the presence of FMD virus (PCR positive) and the
absence of antibody. The Bulgarian Food Safety Agency immediately
started to implement relevant measures including killing and disposal
of the bovines.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country;
zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no
vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: FMD National Reference Laboratory (national
laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 19 Mar 2011 / Negative
Cattle / real-time PCR / 19 Mar 2011 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
